headlines.description: — Kelly Oubre Jr. scored 28 points, and the Charlotte Hornets erased a 21-point first-half deficit to beat the Indiana Pacers 115-109 on Monday night behind a strong finish to snap a six-game home losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oubre, Hornets finish strong, beat Pacers 115-109

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 26 points, DeMar DeRozan had 25 and the Chicago Bulls defeated Joel Embiid and the Philadelphia 76ers 109-105 in double overtime Monday night to snap their eight-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine, DeRozan lead Bulls past 76ers in double overtime

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 57 points in one of the greatest nights in Knicks history. The Minnesota Timberwolves had the most sizzling start in the NBA this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wolves overcome Randle's 57 points, beat Knicks 140-134

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 30 points and Klay Thompson added 29 as the Golden State Warriors snapped an 11-game road skid with a 121-108 win over the Houston Rockets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors down Rockets 121-108 to snap 11-game road skid

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 28 points, including a key layup with 17 seconds left as the Memphis Grizzlies defeated the Dallas Mavericks 112-108 on Monday night in Ja Morant's first game back with the team after an eight-game league suspension.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson scores 28 as Grizzlies rally late to defeat Mavs

headlines.description: — Ochai Agbaji scored a career-high 27 points, including six 3-pointers, to lead the Utah Jazz to a 128-120 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Agbaji scores 27, Jazz hold off Kings for 128-120 victory
